stylometry: We are considering doing a problem with my fathers printing company.  He has a printing press that does basically the same as a copier, but is cheaper and faster to produce when there is a high amount to produce.  At the some time there is a set up cost in making the plates fot the printing, whereas there is a click charge for the copier.  Our group wants to figure out with what type of job, how many items, and how many man hours it takes for us to use the printing press vs. the copier.  What will bring him the least cost to print intern will bring him the most profit.
